# Week 1 — Nmap Commands

## What is Nmap?
Nmap is used to discover open ports and services on a target.
It is the first tool used in almost every penetration test.

## Commands I used today

### nmap 172.17.0.2
Basic scan. Checks top 1000 common ports.
Found: Port 80 open (HTTP)

### nmap -sV 172.17.0.2
Service version scan. Identifies software running on open ports.
Found: Apache httpd 2.4.25 on Debian Linux
Apache 2.4.25 is from 2017 and has known CVEs.

### nmap -sV -oN reports/dvwa-nmap-scan.txt 172.17.0.2
Same scan but saves output to a file.
Always do this on real engagements.

## Important Nmap flags
-sC  : runs default scripts
-p-  : scans all 65535 ports
-A   : aggressive scan
-T4  : faster scan speed
-oN  : save output to file